GATA Pixels is a yield-focused NFT collection built by GATA on Stargaze, designed to experiment with a new NFTfi ownership model combining yield generation, redemption-based liquidity, transparency, and recycling mechanics.

The collection consists of 1111 NFTs where rarity directly impacts yield performance. Unlike traditional NFTs that rely entirely on secondary market liquidity, GATA Pixels introduces structured redemption, allowing holders to exit without depending solely on finding a buyer.

Redeemed NFTs are recycled back into the ecosystem through auctions, creating a continuous loop of ownership, rewards, and redistribution.

The project explores how NFTs can evolve beyond speculative collectibles into reusable, yield-bearing digital assets with measurable performance and transparent participation.

